column2: Note.  Estimates in this table are based on the North American Industry Classification System (NAICS).
Chained (2005) dollar inventory series are calculated to ensure that the chained (2005) dollar change
in inventories for 2005 equals the current-dollar change in inventories for 2005 and that the
average of the 2004 and 2005 end-of-year chain-weighted and fixed-weighted inventories are equal.
Chained (2005) dollar final sales series are calculated as the product of the chain-type quantity
index and the 2005 current-dollar value of the corresponding series, divided by 100.  Because
the formual for the chain-type quantity indexes uses weights of more than one period, the
corresponding chained-dollar estimates are usually not additive.  The residual line is the difference
between the first line and the sum of the most detailed lines for inventories.
